description: This 1967 Chevrolet Camaro is for sale in our Louisville Showroom. So we all know how the story goes, Ford produces the iconic pony car know as the Mustang and all the other automakers jumped on the band wagon to cash in on this phenomenon. Mopar had the Challenger/Cuda, AMC had the AMX and GM had the Camaro/Firebird.  At one point, the Camaro even out sold the mighty Mustang for pony car supremacy. This particular Camaro was owner by the same person, until last year when his buddy bought it off of him. This Camaro originally came with the hide-a-way head lights, but he said they were such a pain that he got rid of them when the car was restored. During the restoration, new rear quarter panels, new floorboards and a new trunk pan were installed. This Camaro RS also received new glass, new emblems, new mirrors and a new interior. The original was replaced with a freshly rebuilt 350 CID Corvette V8 engine. The 4-speed manual transmission has been rebuilt and is the original to the car. The suspension was also addressed during the restoration and disc brakes were added to the front. The Candy Apple Brandywine is in great condition. There is a small dent in the driverÃ¢??s door, paint-less dent repair may be able to get this out. Worst case scenario, the door is fixed by conventional methods then repainted to match the color of Camaro.  If you been looking to get into a nice rust free 1st Gen Camaro RS, but not break the bank doing it, call us before its in somebody elseÃ¢??s garage. Options for these 1967 Chevrolet Camaro RS include; AM/FM Radio, Power Brakes, Power Steering, Seat Belts, Vinyl Interior and Aluminum Alloy Wheels wrapped in Radial Tires. For more information or to schedule an appointment to view this Camaro in person, please call the Louisville showroom at (812)294-1555 or email us directly at Louisville@GatewayClassicCars.com.

description: Some cars are just unmistakably cool from every angle.  One glance at this 1970 Chevrolet Camaro Baldwin-Motion tribute and you know there have been some serious investments in upgrades.  The distinct paint package, performance V8, four-speed stick, and side pipes all tell you this is the coolest Camaro you can gets your hands on!

Baldwin-Motion is mentioned in the same breath as Yenko or Nickey in the Chevrolet communities.  This hallowed performance car name only produced a handful of originals, which means buying one today will require forgoing a large home, and it'll make you nervous every time it leaves the garage.  So the obvious solution is the Camaro you see here.  This 1970 coupe carries the iconic and unique full striping package that came from ordering your Camaro through Motion Performance via Baldwin Chevrolet. Even those who don't recognize this hallmark will quiver at the large side exhaust pipes, huge cowl hood, and super-slick red paint.  But more than just look the part, everything from the shine of the bumpers, to the full-width spoiler let you know the detail work on this one is cut-above.

The deep, dark interior wants you to know this Camaro immediately gets down to business.  You sit down in modern ProCar bucket seats that hug your body better than anything from the '70s ever could.  Your left hand gets the grippy thin factory-style steering wheel, and your right one may never want to leave the Hurst shifter.  You have all the right gauges, including a SunPro auxiliary trio under the dash.  All of this is designed to get your heart racing even before you twist the key and hear those side pipes roar.

Because these B-M Camaros were all about the monster motor, you'll love showing off the engine bay.  The 350 cubic-inch V8 is dressed to impress with both plenty of shine from the polished components and a bit of dark attitude with the fender walls and air topper.  But what you and the other enthusiasts will love the most is the proper Motion valve covers.  This V8 backs up its powerful looks with performance upgrades such as the bored .60 over kit, Holley four-barrel carburetor, Edelbrock intake, and a full header package.  The coupe makes all the right muscle car growls, and you're in complete control of this sound and fury thanks to the four-speed manual transmission.  This is a muscle machine made to go hit the road with great features like thick sway bars front & rear, power steering, front disc brakes, and BF Goodrich T/As on proper Z-28 style wheels.

Your heart will skip a beat every time the ferocious exhaust fires up in your garage.  This Camaro comes with all the admiration of a hallowed classic American muscle nameplate, and more importantly, there's no stress when you want to go out and have a little fun.  Don't miss out on this total package classic, call today!
title: 1970 Chevrolet Camaro

description: This 1967 Chevrolet Camaro 2 Door Hardtop
(Stock # F13195)
is available in our Fairfield, CA showroom and any inquiries may be directed to us at

Sales@SpecialtySales.com

If you’re looking for a gorgeous muscle car that’s ready to hit the roads today, then check out this 1967 Chevrolet Camaro 2 Door Hardtop with fresh Blue Effect exterior paint and a black interior. It features an upgraded 350 cid V-8 engine under the hood with a Holley carburetor, stock manifolds, a dual exhaust, a Hurst shifter, 2.73 gears in the rear and a Turbo 350 automatic transmission. It also has American Racing wheels, front bucket seats, a great sound system and to much more to list…you must see this one in person to really appreciate it.

The current owner of this 1967 Chevrolet Camaro purchased it way back in 1983 while he was still in high school, and this muscle car has been the first true love of his life. He has always kept it in great condition and he recently tuned it up and added a new gas tank and radiator as well, so it’s little surprise that this one drives great and sounds amazing. The 350 crate engine is approximately 10 years old with around 97,000 miles on it.

In terms of condition, this 1967 Camaro shows minor imperfections in the paint and the interior. It is definitely above the typical driver standard, although the next owner would have to do some minor refreshing to get this one back to true show quality. There is really nothing to detract from its overall curb appeal though and it can be enjoyed right away.

Overall, this driver-quality 1967 Chevrolet Camaro Hardtop is a gorgeous automobile that any muscle car fanatic would be proud to drive. Given the collectability of these examples and the good performance, there’s no way it lasts for long at the current price point.
